{
  "local_port": 44980,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Sure! Here are a few simple and delicious recipes that use 4 ounces of steak:\n\n1. **Steak Salad:**\n   - Ingredients:\n     - 4 ounces of steak (such as sirloin or flank)\n     - Mixed greens (spinach, arugula, etc.)\n     - Cherry tomatoes (halved)\n     - Cucumber slices\n     - Red onion (thinly sliced)\n     - Feta cheese (crumbled)\n     - Balsamic vinaigrette (for dressing)\n   - Instructions:\n     1. Season the steak with salt and pepper, and cook to your desired doneness (grill, pan-sear, or broil).\n     2. Let the steak rest for a few minutes, then thinly slice it.\n     3. Combine the mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber slices, red onion, and feta cheese in a bowl.\n     4. Top the salad with the sliced steak and drizzle with balsamic vinaigrette.\n\n2. **Steak Tacos:**\n   - Ingredients:\n     - 4 ounces of steak (such as skirt or flank)\n     - 4 small tortillas\n     - 1 avocado (sliced)\n     - 1/4 cup chopped cilantro\n     - 1/4 cup diced onions\n     - Lime wedges\n     - Salsa (optional)\n     - Salt and pepper\n   - Instructions:\n     1. Season the steak with salt and pepper, and cook to your desired doneness (grill, pan-sear, or broil).\n     2. Let the steak rest for a few minutes, then thinly slice or dice it.\n     3. Warm the tortillas in a pan or microwave.\n     4. Place the sliced or diced steak on the tortillas.\n     5. Top with avocado slices, chopped cilantro, diced onions, and a squeeze of lime juice.\n     6. Add salsa if desired.\n\n3. **Steak Stir-Fry:**\n   - Ingredients:\n     - 4 ounces of steak (such as flank or sirloin)\n     - 1 cup mixed vegetables (broccoli, bell peppers, snap peas, etc.)\n     - 1 garlic clove (minced)\n     - 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n     - 1 teaspoon sesame oil\n     - Cooked rice or noodles (optional)\n   - Instructions:\n     1. Thinly slice the steak into strips.\n     2. Heat sesame oil in a pan over medium-high heat.\n     3. Add the minced garlic and cook for about 30 seconds.\n     4. Add the steak strips and stir-fry until browned and cooked to your desired doneness.\n     5. Add the mixed vegetables and soy sauce, and stir-fry until the vegetables are tender-crisp.\n     6. Serve over cooked rice or noodles if desired.\n\n4. **Steak and Eggs:**\n   - Ingredients:\n     - 4 ounces of steak (such as rib-eye or sirloin)\n     - 2 large eggs\n     - 1 tablespoon butter or oil\n     - Salt and pepper\n   - Instructions:\n     1. Season the steak with salt and pepper, and cook to your desired doneness (grill, pan-sear, or broil).\n     2. Let the steak rest for a few minutes, then thinly slice it.\n     3. Heat butter or oil in a pan over medium heat.\n     4. Crack the eggs into the pan and cook to your desired doneness (scrambled, sunny-side up, etc.).\n     5. Serve the steak slices with the cooked eggs.\n\nFeel free to customize these recipes with your favorite ingredients and seasonings!",
